This paper deals with the problem of selecting a set of seed nodes in social networks to maximize the influence spread within a given budget. This problem is related to social networks, data structures, artificial intelligence, and computational engineering. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
